column5: Made it out to the "spot" on wed. The group as you can see from Shelly's report were already into the fish. we set up and no longer then 5min and my friend chris had her first whitie of her life through the hole a nice 5lbs'er we made out well getting 4 fish each and loosing a few more. I finally got a 10+ lbs laker quick shot and back down the hole. what a great day to be on the water. no definatly no shortage of fish
nICE wtg out there great looking pictures
Another soild report. Congrats on the fish.  -R
That's a beauty Laker ! Great to hear she's still swimmin...
Big Cliff and I should be so lucky tomorrow...WTG !
Some nice looking fish there, definitely looked like a great day out on the ice
very nice looking laker, thanks for sharing.
good stuff... I was out there today no lakers but just smashed the whities
